title: Self Help
guest_stars: Dr. Joyce Brothers, Rich Hall, Anka Radakovich
synopsis: Helping to rehabilitate Zorak, Space Ghost welcomes psychiatrist Dr. Joyce Brothers, who ends up being more concerned about him. Later, comic Rich Hall gives Space Ghost pointers on how to pick up women that are immediately used by Zorak and Moltar to impress author Anka Radakovich.

transcript.speaker: Moltar
transcript.dialogue: I have an addiction to... fire.

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: Playing with fire can really be harmful to you, to me, to your studio, to everything that you hold dear.

transcript.speaker: Moltar
transcript.dialogue: (leans forward, hits the screen with his helmet, breaking it)

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: (invisos in) ¡Hola! I am Space Ghost. On this show I've gathered a panel of therapists to help Zorak. (lowers voice) He's evil.

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: (invisos in) ¡Hola! (laughs) Alrighty! My first guest is Dr. Joyce Brothers. You may have seen her on such shows as "Merv Griffin", "Mike Douglas", "Parker Lewis Can't Lose", "Tic Tac Dough", "Mr. Belvidere", "The X-Men", "The X-Files", "ALF", "The Tonight Show", and "True Stories of the Highway Patrol".

transcript.speaker: Zorak
transcript.dialogue: (sighs) Page two. "Bay Watch", "The $5 Pyramid", "The $20 Pyramid", "The $100 Pyramid", ...

transcript.speaker: Zorak
transcript.dialogue: ... "Joker's Wild", "Weekend at Bernie's", "The Four Hundred Blows", ...

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: Welcome to the show, Dr. Brothers.

transcript.speaker: Zorak
transcript.dialogue: ... "Flubber", "Clockwork Orange", "Chitty Chitty Bang Bang", "The Man from Snowy River"...

transcript.speaker: Zorak
transcript.dialogue: Why are you here? (continues to talk in background)

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: Because people need so much help.

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: Correct! So, what's new, Dr. Brothers?

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: Everything. Uh, I have a new book, called "Positive Plus, The Practical Plan for Liking Yourself Better", and I know, Space Ghost, there's no way you could like yourself better than you do.

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: Not even for money. Hey, isn't Zorak handsome and nice?

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: (in low voice) Dr. Brothers, can you work with me here?

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: I'm trying to mend his evil ways.

transcript.speaker: Zorak
transcript.dialogue: Eh, he's good, don't you think?

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: Do you have any aspirin, doc?

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: I'm sorry, I didn't hear you.

transcript.speaker: Zorak
transcript.dialogue: Hello America, page two, and that man was Walt Disney, and that's the rest of, the story. (keeps talking in background)

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: (in low voice) I said, I'm rehabilitating Zorak, he's really quite evil. Can you help me?

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: If he's an evil locust, then he's only evil every seven years, so, just enjoy him between the seven years.

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: No, but I can help them understand their minds, and that's what I'm trying to do with you, Space Ghost.

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: Me? I'm fine! He's got the problem!

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: Well, I'm not so sure you're okay, but the idea...

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: Of course I'm okay, I'm Space Ghost!

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: The idea is that people validate one another, ...

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: Psychobabble. (Joyce stops talking) Look, lady, I called you in to help Zorak, not me! You think I have the problem?

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: Well, that is a great possibility.

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: (pause) How long have you hated men?

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: (in studio) And, your mask makes it really very difficult for people to divine your motivation.

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: Your motivation, for all we know, may not be as open as your publicity allows us to think.

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: Yes, uh, you know, have you ever seen an ink blot?

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: I think they're fun to watch...

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: ...but I don't think they're psychic at all. I think some people...

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: ...are willing to look at all the information...

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: On the way to Panama City!

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: I'm sorry, so what about these ink stains you were blathering about?

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: Well, you know, you project all your emotions onto that ink blot...

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: You know, we really are trained in every culture to look at people...

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: So if you ask a little child who hasn't had...

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: You're... not gonna charge me for this, are you?

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: Well, umm, actually, it would, I would send you a double bill because you have a split personality.

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: Ohhhh! So now I'm a schizo?

transcript.speaker: Joyce Brothers
transcript.dialogue: (pause) It's very possible, um, you would know better than anyone else.

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: (chuckles) That's preposterous. I am not, nor have I ever been, a schizophrenic. (British voice) That's not true. (regular voice) You be quiet. (British voice) Who's the lady? (regular voice) Shut up! (British voice) Aren't you gonna introduce me?

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: I heard that! (British voice) No, you didn't!

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: (laughs) Alrighty! We're back! (pause) Hey Zorak, that Dr. Brothers sure was a nut!

transcript.speaker: Zorak
transcript.dialogue: I thought she was incredibly informative and had many insightful observations about your behavior.

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: What!? Oh, I see. You think I'm crazy, don't you?

transcript.speaker: Rich Hall
transcript.dialogue: That's enough, really, let's, uh, let's, let's draw the line there.

transcript.speaker: Rich Hall
transcript.dialogue: Thank you. (Moltar pulls the lever, sending Rich to the studio)

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: (in Clint Eastwood voice) Buckle up for safety.

transcript.speaker: Rich Hall
transcript.dialogue: Uh, it's a hundred and twenty eight pages of, uh, of all the major dysfunctions on our planet...

transcript.speaker: Rich Hall
transcript.dialogue: ... uh, I'm trying to kinda, you know, put the fun back into dysfunction.

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: Oh, I get it! Fun into dysfunction!

transcript.speaker: Rich Hall
transcript.dialogue: A sense of humor's very important, Space Ghost, and I can see that you're desperately trying to develop one, and that's good.

transcript.speaker: Rich Hall
transcript.dialogue: And, and you look very, very stylish in your cape, by the way.

transcript.speaker: Rich Hall
transcript.dialogue: Oh, no, I'm sorry, I don't mean to make you uncomfortable. No, really, I mean, I'm just sayin' that from uh, one guy to another, you know.

transcript.speaker: Rich Hall
transcript.dialogue: Well, Space Ghost, you have to become a little more comfortable with your sexuality, and a little more confident in it, you know. I'm just giving you a compliment, it's not like I'm comin' on to you or anything, you know.

transcript.speaker: Rich Hall
transcript.dialogue: I mean, you're a superhero, I think you need some superhero confidence, in your, uh, sexuality.

transcript.speaker: Rich Hall
transcript.dialogue: You need to, uh, you need to watch some more TV.

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: More TV, you don't say? Any certain way I should watch TV?

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: Would you like to wear the cape, Rich?

transcript.speaker: Rich Hall
transcript.dialogue: No, I don't do sniglets anymore, uh, they're dead. Put 'em in the garage.

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: Make up a sniglet for Zorak.

transcript.speaker: Rich Hall
transcript.dialogue: (annoyed) I'm gonna let you enjoy your little self referential moment of mirth there, Space Ghost.

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: How about, Mantis Do Gooder. Is that a swell sniglet or what, Rich?

transcript.speaker: Rich Hall
transcript.dialogue: (more annoyed) Are there prizes for these questions?

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: This isn't a game show, Mr. Hall

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: Thank you. Rich, tell us about your super powers.

transcript.speaker: Rich Hall
transcript.dialogue: Uh, I have none, and I'm totally defenseless at this point to whatever, uh, assault Earth decides to commit against me, uh, I'm just a victim.

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: A victim of your own self pity.

transcript.speaker: Rich Hall
transcript.dialogue: No, I just feel like, uh, I know my place on the planet and it's, it's very tiny, I think that...

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: Okay. Why won't women talk to me?

transcript.speaker: Rich Hall
transcript.dialogue: Well, the first thing that you need to do, is, uh, go all out and lie.

transcript.speaker: Rich Hall
transcript.dialogue: Use your imagination, just tell women what they want to hear, you know, you can always cover your tracks later.

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: But Rich, I always tell the truth.

transcript.speaker: Rich Hall
transcript.dialogue: That's not what women want to hear. They wanna hear you drummed for Pearl Jam. Yeah.

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: (zaps Rich off screen) Now, let's see, what's next? (looking at his hand) Hey, look at my hand! (covering & uncovering his face) Open, close, open, close, open ...

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: Zorak... I don't feel well, you do it.

transcript.speaker: Anka Radakovich
transcript.dialogue: Oh yeah, (smooch smooch) can I give you a kiss? (puckers)

transcript.speaker: Moltar
transcript.dialogue: Bye bye. (throws lever) I love you.

transcript.speaker: Zorak
transcript.dialogue: Umm... er... uh... you are a human.

transcript.speaker: Zorak
transcript.dialogue: You are a pretty female human.

transcript.speaker: Zorak
transcript.dialogue: Mm Hmmm, pretty pretty female human.

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: Anka, I'm the drummer for Pearl Jam!

transcript.speaker: Anka Radakovich
transcript.dialogue: Well, I just wrote a book.

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: Well, I drum for a band.

transcript.speaker: Anka Radakovich
transcript.dialogue: Well, I just wrote a book.

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: Well I can speak French really loud!

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: Je parle français très fort, no?

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: Je peux ouvrir une boite d'épinards avec les muscles de mon derrière! (laughs) (subdued) I used to be so pretty... in Paris. (French cafe music) (inset picture of Space Ghost in a dress)

transcript.speaker: Zorak
transcript.dialogue: So, what do you think of me, human?

transcript.speaker: Anka Radakovich
transcript.dialogue: Um, I think you're masculine but sensitive...

transcript.speaker: Zorak
transcript.dialogue: You do not know me, human! I am evil, therefore I am lonely. I'm just a lonely... drummer for Pearl Jam.

transcript.speaker: Moltar
transcript.dialogue: I see what you're doing! Putting the lonely mantis routine on to get the girl. You're lying!

transcript.speaker: Space Ghost
transcript.dialogue: (finishing "Frère Jacques") Dang dong dang! Dang dong dang!

transcript.speaker: Zorak
transcript.dialogue: At least I have a head!
